@c    to the priests, to the storehouse of our God, and the tithes of our
@c    ground to the Levites.  The Levites also shall receive the tithes of our
@c    works out of all the cities.

@c    10:38. And the priest the son of Aaron shall be with the Levites in the
@c    tithes of the Levites, and the Levites shall offer the tithe of their
@c    tithes in the house of our God, to the storeroom into the treasure
@c    house.

@c    10:39. For the children of Israel and the children of Levi shall carry
@c    to the treasury the firstfruits of corn, of wine, and of oil:  and the
@c    sanctified vessels shall be there, and the priests, and the singing
@c    men, and the porters, and ministers, and we will not forsake the house
@c    of our God.



@c    2 Esdras Chapter 11


@c    Who were the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and the other cities.

@c    11:1. And the princes of the people dwelt at Jerusalem:  but the rest of
@c    the people cast lots, to take one part in ten to dwell in Jerusalem the
@c    holy city, and nine parts in the other cities.

@c    11:2. And the people blessed all the men that willingly offered
@c    themselves to dwell in Jerusalem.

@c    11:3. These therefore are the chief men of the province, who dwelt in
@c    Jerusalem, and in the cities of Juda.  And every one dwelt in his
@c    possession, in their cities:  Israel, the priests, the Levites, the
@c    Nathinites, and the children of the servants of Solomon.

@c    11:4. And in Jerusalem there dwelt some of the children of Juda, and
@c    some of the children of Benjamin:  of the children of Juda, Athaias the
@c    son of Aziam, the son of Zacharias, the son of Amarias, the son of
@c    Saphatias, the son of Malaleel:  of the sons of Phares,

@c    11:5. Maasia the son of Baruch, the son of Cholhoza, the son of Hazia,
@c    the son of Adaia, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zacharias, the son of
@c    the Silonite:

@c    11:6. All these the sons of Phares, who dwelt in Jerusalem, were four
@c    hundred sixty-eight valiant men.

@c    11:7. And these are the children of Benjamin:  Sellum the son of
@c    Mosollam, the son of Joed, the son of Phadaia, the son of Colaia, the
@c    son of Masia, the son of Etheel, the son of Isaia.

@c    11:8. And after him Gebbai, Sellai, nine hundred twenty-eight.

@c    11:9. And Joel the son of Zechri their ruler, and Judas the son of
@c    Senua was second over the city.

@c    11:10. And of the priests Idaia the son of Joarib, Jachin,

@c    11:11. Saraia the son of Helcias, the son of Mosollam, the son of
@c    Sadoc, the son of Meraioth, the son of Achitob the prince of the house
@c    of God,

@c    11:12. And their brethren that do the works of the temple:  eight
@c    hundred twenty-two.  And Adaia the son of Jeroham, the son of Phelelia,
@c    the son of Amsi, the son of Zacharias, the son of Pheshur, the son of
@c    Melchias,

@c    11:13. And his brethren the chiefs of the fathers:  two hundred
@c    forty-two.  And Amassai the son of Azreel, the son of Ahazi, the son of
@c    Mosollamoth, the son of Emmer,

@c    11:14. And their brethren who were very mighty, a hundred twenty-eight:
@c    and their ruler Zabdiel son of the mighty.

@c    11:15. And of the Levites Semeia the son of Hasub, the son of Azaricam,
@c    the son of Hasabia, the son of Boni,

@c    11:16. And Sabathai and Jozabed, who were over all the outward business
@c    of the house of God, of the princes of the Levites,

@c    11:17. And Mathania the son of Micha, the son of Zebedei, the son of
@c    Asaph, was the principal man to praise, and to give glory in prayer,
@c    and Becbecia, the second, one of his brethren, and Abda the son of
@c    Samua, the son of Galal, the son of Idithun.

@c    11:18. All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred eighty-four.

@c    11:19. And the porters, Accub, Telmon, and their brethren, who kept the
@c    doors:  a hundred seventy-two.

@c    11:20. And the rest of Israel, the priests and the Levites were in all
@c    the cities of Juda, every man in his possession.

@c    11:21. And the Nathinites, that dwelt in Ophel, and Siaha, and Gaspha
@c    of the Nathinites.

@c    11:22. And the overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem, was Azzi the son
@c    of Bani, the son of Hasabia, the son of Mathania, the son of Micha.  Of
@c    the sons of Asaph, were the singing men in the ministry of the house of
@c    God.

@c    11:23. For the king's commandment was concerning them, and an order
@c    among the singing men day by day.

@c    11:24. And Phathahia the son of Mesezebel of the children of Zara the
@c    son of Juda was at the hand of the king, in all matters concerning the
@c    people,

@c    11:25. And in the houses through all their countries.  Of the children
@c    of Juda some dwelt at Cariath-Arbe, and in the villages thereof:  and at
@c    Dibon, and in the villages thereof:  and at Cabseel, and in the villages
@c    thereof.

@c    11:26. And at Jesue, and at Molada, and at Bethphaleth,

@c    11:27. And at Hasersuel, and at Bersabee, and in the villages thereof,

@c    11:28. And at Siceleg, and at Mochona, and in the villages thereof,

@c    11:29. And at Remmon, and at Saraa, and at Jerimuth,

@c    11:30. Zanoa, Odollam, and in their villages, at Lachis and its
@c    dependencies, and at Azeca and the villages thereof.  And they dwelt
@c    from Bersabee unto the valley of Ennom.

@c    11:31. And the children of Benjamin, from Geba, at Mechmas, and at Hai,
@c    and at Bethel, and in the villages thereof,

@c    11:32. At Anathoth, Nob, Anania,

@c    11:33. Asor, Rama, Gethaim,

@c    11:34. Hadid, Seboim, and Neballat, Lod,

@c    11:35. And Ono the valley of craftsmen.

@c    11:36. And of the Levites were portions of Juda and Benjamin.



@c    2 Esdras Chapter 12


@c    The priests, and Levites that came up with Zorobabel.  The succession of
@c    high priests:  the solemnity of the dedication of the wall.

@c    12:1. Now these are the priests and the Levites, that went up with
@c    Zorobabel the son of Salathiel, and Josue:  Saraia, Jeremias, Esdras,

@c    12:2. Amaria, Melluch, Hattus,

@c    12:3. Sebenias, Rheum, Merimuth,

@c    12:4. Addo, Genthon, Abia,

@c    12:5. Miamin, Madia, Belga,

@c    12:6. Semeia, and Joiarib, Idaia, Sellum Amoc, Helcias,

@c    12:7. Idaia.  These were the chief of the priests, and of their brethren
@c    in the days of Josue.

@c    12:8. And the Levites, Jesua, Bennui, Cedmihel, Sarebia, Juda,
@c    Mathanias, they and their brethren were over the hymns:

@c    12:9. And Becbecia, and Hanni, and their brethren every one in his
@c    office.

@c    12:10. And Josue begot Joacim, and Joacim begot Eliasib, and Eliasib
@c    begot Joiada,

@c    12:11. And Joiada begot Jonathan and Jonathan begot Jeddoa.

@c    12:12. And in the days of Joacim the priests and heads of the families
@c    were:  Of Saraia, Maraia:  of Jeremias, Hanania:

@c    12:13. Of Esdras, Mosollam:  and of Amaria, Johanan:

@c    12:14. Of Milicho, Jonathan:  of Sebenia, Joseph:

@c    12:15. Of Haram, Edna:  of Maraioth, Helci:

@c    12:16. Of Adaia, Zacharia:  of Genthon, Mosollam:

@c    12:17. Of Abia, Zechri:  of Miamin and Moadia, Phelti:

@c    12:18. Of Belga, Sammua of Semaia, Jonathan:

@c    12:19. Of Joiarib, Mathanai:  of Jodaia, Azzi:

@c    12:20. Of Sellai, Celai:  of Amoc, Heber:

@c    12:21. Of Helcias, Hasebia:  of Idaia, Nathanael.

@c    12:22. The Levites the chiefs of the families in the days of Eliasib,
@c    and Joiada, and Johanan, and Jeddoa, were recorded, and the priests in
@c    the reign of Darius the Persian.

@c    12:23. The sons of Levi, heads of the families were written in the book
@c    of Chronicles, even unto the days of Jonathan the son of Eliasib.

@c    12:24. Now the chief of the Levites were Hasebia, Serebia, and Josue
@c    the son of Cedmihel:  and their brethren by their courses, to praise and
@c    to give thanks according to the commandment of David the man of God,
@c    and to wait equally in order.

@c    12:25. Mathania, and Becbecia, Obedia, and Mosollam, Telmon, Accub,
@c    were keepers of the gates and of the entrances before the gates.

@c    12:26. These were in the days of Joacim the son of Josue, the son of
@c    Josedec, and in the days of Nehemias the governor, and of Esdras the
@c    priest and scribe.

@c    12:27. And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the
@c    Levites out of all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem, and to
@c    keep the dedication, and to rejoice with thanksgiving, and with
@c    singing, and with cymbals, and psalteries and harps.

@c    12:28. And the sons of the singing men were gathered together out of
@c    the plain country about Jerusalem, and out of the villages of
@c    Nethuphati,

@c    12:29. And from the house of Galgal, and from the countries of Geba and
@c    Azmaveth:  for the singing men had built themselves villages round about
@c    Jerusalem.

@c    12:30. And the priests and the Levites were purified, and they purified
@c    the people, and the gates, and the wall.

@c    12:31. And I made the princes of Juda go up upon the wall, and I
@c    appointed two great choirs to give praise.  And they went on the right
@c    hand upon the wall toward the dung gate.

@c    12:32. And after them went Osaias, and half of the princes of Juda,

@c    12:33. And Azarias, Esdras, and Mosollam, Judas, and Benjamin, and
@c    Semeia, and Jeremias.

@c    12:34. And of the sons of the priests with trumpets, Zacharias the son
@c    of Jonathan, the son of Semeia, the son of Mathania, the son of
@c    Michaia, the son of Zechur, the son of Asaph,

@c    12:35. And his brethren Semeia, and Azareel, Malalai, Galalai, Maai,
@c    Nathanael, and Judas, and Hanani, with the musical instruments of David
@c    the man of God:  and Esdras the scribe before them at the fountain gate.

@c    12:36. And they went up over against them by the stairs of the city of
@c    David, at the going up of the wall of the house of David, and to the
@c    water gate eastward:

@c    12:37. And the second choir of them that gave thanks went on the
@c    opposite side, and I after them, and the half of the people upon the
@c    wall, and upon the tower of the furnaces, even to the broad wall,

@c    12:38. And above the gate of Ephraim, and above the old gate, and above
@c    the fish gate and the tower of Hananeel, and the tower of Emath, and
@c    even to the flock gate:  and they stood still in the watch gate.

@c    12:39. And the two choirs of them that gave praise stood still at the
@c    house of God, and I and the half of the magistrates with me.

@c    12:40. And the priests, Eliachim, Maasia, Miamin, Michea, Elioenai,
@c    Zacharia, Hanania with trumpets,

@c    12:41. And Maasia, and Semeia, and Eleazar, and Azzi, and Johanan, and
@c    Melchia, and Elam, and Ezer.  And the singers sung loud, and Jezraia was
@c    their overseer:

@c    12:42. And they sacrificed on that day great sacrifices, and they
@c    rejoiced:  for God had made them joyful with great joy:  their wives also
@c    and their children rejoiced, and the joy of Jerusalem was heard afar
@c    off.

@c    12:43. They appointed also in that day men over the storehouses of the
@c    treasure, for the libations, and for the firstfruits, and for the
@c    tithes, that the rulers of the city might bring them in by them in
@c    honour of thanksgiving, for the priests and Levites:  for Juda was
@c    joyful in the priests and Levites that assisted.

@c    12:44. And they kept the watch of their God, and the observance of
@c    expiation, and the singing men, and the porters, according to the
@c    commandment of David, and of Solomon his son.

@c    12:45. For in the days of David and Asaph from the beginning there were
@c    chief singers appointed, to praise with canticles, and give thanks to
@c    God.

@c    12:46. And all Israel, in the days of Zorobabel, and in the days of
@c    Nehemias gave portions to the singing men, and to the porters, day by
@c    day, and they sanctified the Levites, and the Levites sanctified the
@c    sons of Aaron.

@c    Sanctified. . .That is, they gave them that which by the law was set
@c    aside, and sanctified for their use.



@c    2 Esdras Chapter 13


@c    Divers abuses are reformed.

@c    13:1. And on that day they read in the book of Moses in the hearing of
@c    the people:  and therein was found written, that the Ammonites and the
@c    Moabites should not come in to the church of God for ever:

@c    13:2. Because they met not the children of Israel with bread and water:
@c    and they hired against them Balaam, to curse them, and our God turned
@c    the curse into blessing.

@c    13:3. And it came to pass, when they had heard the law, that they
@c    separated every stranger from Israel.

@c    13:4. And over this thing was Eliasib the priest, who was set over the
@c    treasury of the house of our God, and was near akin to Tobias.

@c    Over this thing, etc. . .Or, he was faulty in this thing, or in this
@c    kind.

@c    13:5. And he made him a great storeroom, where before him they laid up
@c    gifts, and frankincense, and vessels, and the tithes of the corn, of
@c    the wine, and of the oil, the portions of the Levites, and of the
@c    singing men, and of the porters, and the firstfruits of the priests.

@c    13:6. But in all this time I was not in Jerusalem, because in the two
@c    and thirtieth year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon, I went to the king,
@c    and after certain days I asked the king:

@c    13:7. And I came to Jerusalem, and I understood the evil that Eliasib
@c    had done for Tobias, to make him a storehouse in the courts of the
@c    house of God.

@c    13:8. And it seemed to me exceeding evil.  And I cast forth the vessels
@c    of the house of Tobias out of the storehouse.

@c    13:9. And I commanded and they cleansed again the vessels of the house
@c    of God, the sacrifice, and the frankincense.

@c    13:10. And I perceived that the portions of the Levites had not been
@c    given them:  and that the Levites, and the singing men, and they that
@c    ministered were fled away every man to his own country:

@c    13:11. And I pleaded the matter against the magistrates, and said:  Why
@c    have we forsaken the house of God?  And I gathered them together, and I
@c    made them to stand in their places.

@c    13:12. And all Juda brought the tithe of the corn, and the wine, and
@c    the oil into the storehouses.

@c    13:13. And we set over the storehouses Selemias the priest, and Sadoc
@c    the scribe, and of the Levites Phadaia, and next to them Hanan the son
@c    of Zachur, the son of Mathania:  for they were approved as faithful, and
@c    to them were committed the portions of their brethren.

@c    13:14. Remember me, O my God, for this thing, and wipe not out my
@c    kindnesses, which I have done relating to the house of my God and his
@c    ceremonies.

@c    13:15. In those days I saw in Juda some treading the presses on the
@c    sabbath, and carrying sheaves, and lading asses with wine, and grapes,
@c    and figs, and all manner of burthens, and bringing them into Jerusalem
@c    on the sabbath day.  And I charged them that they should sell on a day
@c    on which it was lawful to sell.

@c    13:16. Some Tyrians also dwelt there, who brought fish, and all manner
@c    of wares:  and they sold them on the sabbaths to the children of Juda in
@c    Jerusalem.

@c    13:17. And I rebuked the chief men of Juda, and said to them:  What is
@c    this evil thing that you are doing, profaning the sabbath day:

@c    13:18. Did not our fathers do these things, and our God brought all
@c    this evil upon us, and upon this city?  And you bring more wrath upon
@c    Israel by violating the sabbath.

@c    13:19. And it came to pass, that when the gates of Jerusalem were at
@c    rest on the sabbath day, I spoke:  and they shut the gates, and I
@c    commanded that they should not open them till after the sabbath:  and I
@c    set some of my servants at the gates, that none should bring in
@c    burthens on the sabbath day.

@c    13:20. So the merchants, and they that sold all kinds of wares, stayed
@c    without Jerusalem, once or twice.

@c    13:21. And I charged them, and I said to them:  Why stay you before the
@c    wall?  if you do so another time, I will lay hands on you.  And from that
@c    time they came no more on the sabbath.

@c    13:22. I spoke also to the Levites that they should be purified, and
@c    should come to keep the gates, and to sanctify the sabbath day:  for
@c    this also remember me, O my God, and spare me according to the
@c    multitude of thy tender mercies.

@c    13:23. In those days also I saw Jews that married wives, women of
@c    Azotus, and of Ammon, and of Moab.

@c    13:24. And their children spoke half in the speech of Azotus, and could
@c    not speak the Jews' language, but they spoke according to the language
@c    of this and that people.

@c    13:25. And I chid them, and laid my curse upon them.  And I beat some of
@c    them, and shaved off their hair, and made them swear by God that they
@c    would not give their daughters to their sons, nor take their daughters
@c    for their sons, nor for themselves, saying:

@c    13:26. Did not Solomon king of Israel sin in this kind of thing:  and
@c    surely among many nations, there was not a king like him, and he was
@c    beloved of his God, and God made him king over all Israel:  and yet
@c    women of other countries brought even him to sin.

@c    13:27. And shall we also be disobedient and do all this great evil to
@c    transgress against our God, and marry strange women:

@c    13:28. And one of the sons of Joiada the son of Eliasib the high
@c    priest, was son in law to Sanaballat the Horonite, and I drove him from
@c    me.

@c    13:29. Remember them, O Lord my God, that defile the priesthood, and
@c    the law of priests and Levites.

@c    13:30. So I separated from them all strangers, and I appointed the
@c    courses of the priests and the Levites, every man in his ministry:

@c    13:31. And for the offering of wood at times appointed, and for the
@c    firstfruits:  remember me, O my God, unto good.  Amen.
